      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index validation against in-vitro measurements",
      "description": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against in-vitro measurements from five flow-speed operating points (2.0–4.5 L/min, 2500–4000 RPM). Lagrangian red blood cell tracking with power-law damage accumulation model. Predicted NIH within ±18% of measured values across all five points; mean absolute error 9.3%. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion satisfied for all candidate operating conditions. Validation data sourced from FDA benchmark dataset (CDRH-2013-CFD-Pump)."
    },
    {
