      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Turbulence model sensitivity — SST k-ω vs. realizable k-ε",
      "description": "Comparison of SST k-ω and realizable k-ε turbulence closures for the primary operating point (3.0 L/min, 3500 RPM). Velocity profiles at three axial planes show < 5% deviation between models. NIH predictions differ by 7.2%, within the accepted model-form uncertainty envelope for MRL 2. SST k-ω selected as primary closure based on superior near-wall resolution.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
