    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2 (Class II, medium model influence, high decision consequence). Six factors appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 requirements for MRL 2. Validation evidence demonstrates NIH predictions within ±18% of experimental measurements across all five operating points, satisfying the ±25% acceptance criterion. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 confirmed for all candidate worst-case operating conditions. Total combined uncertainty budget (discretization + model form + input) estimated at ±8.4% NIH, within acceptable bounds for the COU decision. Credibility assessment supports regulatory submission for Class II CPB device 510(k) clearance.",
